List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2000/2/5/46

	It is available for linux-2.2.5-15 (RH 6.0) for intel pentium
family as a patch. 
	
http://www2.csa.iisc.ernet.in/~mansoor/proj/index.html
or 	
http://agni.csa.iisc.ernet.in/~mansoor/proj/index.html
Uses:
Resource containers seperate out protection domain from resource
principal.
Proper accounting done for processing in interrupt contexts.
Allocates resources in predictable manner. (Can be used for multimedia
scheduling by putting X-server process and multimedia process in the same
resource container).
Supports container specific schedulers. Supports multiple scheduling
classes.
- mansoor
